title: Ask HN: Do you see any of the 'alternative social media' going mainstream?
text: Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram are all losing mindshare. TikTok is a Trojan horse. The others are big in tech circles and the reddit-savvy crowd, barely registering in most people's lives.

Ask HN: How many HN users are moving to Mastodon from Twitter?
text:
Firstly, I used to love Twitter!

However, I will move to Mastodon due to the recent spate of haphazard rule changes, bugs, and unstable systems. I have noticed many problems, especially with the Android Twitter app.

What is the take of the HN community on moving to Mastodon, especially after Paul G was banned?
